div.p:
1
.
CW
sends a
LogsRequest
to
Ag.A
containing the Workload Instance names for the workloads it wants to collect the logs from.

2.
Ag.A
redirects the message to the
Svr
.

3.
Svr
redirects the message to all the connected agents.

4.
Ag.B
receives the message and stores subscriptions for the logs of the requested workloads, starting the collection of the logs.

div.p:
1
. The subscription in
Ag.B
includes the process that receives the logs from the workloads, thus
Ag.B
receives logs from the workloads
W1
,
W2
...

2.
Ag.B
redirects the
LogsResponse
to the
Svr
.

3. The
Svr
redirects the
LogsResponse
to
Ag.A
.

4.
Ag.A
redirects the
LogsResponse
to
CW
.

div.p:
1.
CW
sends a
LogsCancelRequest
to
Ag.A
with the same request id as the initial
LogsRequest
.

2.
Ag.A
redirects the message to the
Svr
.

3.
Svr
redirects the message to all the connected agents.

4.
Ag.B
receives the message and removes the subscription, thus closing the process collecting the logs.
